What is Workplace Bias?

Unconscious or conscious judgments that affect decisions and interactions at work.
Types of Bias:

Gender, Racial, and Affinity Bias (favoring those similar to us).
Why It Matters:

Bias limits opportunities and reduces fairness in the workplace.
Session Goal:

Understand how to recognize and address bias.
Learn simple steps to create a more inclusive and fair work environment.


Homework Reflection
Reflect on the following quote before our next session:

“Fearlessness is not the absence of fear. It’s the mastery of fear. It’s about getting up one more time than we fall down.”
– Arianna Huffington

Think about how fear of challenging biases or speaking up may have impacted you or others in the workplace.
How can overcoming this fear help you navigate bias and create meaningful change?
